✅ What are Roles in Ansible?
    Roles in Ansible are a way to organize your playbooks into reusable, structured components.
    Instead of writing one big playbook, you split it into smaller parts called roles.
creating roles
-------------
cmd: ansible-galaxy init role-name   --  this will create a directory having files also below how it looks like

    └── role-name
        ├── README.md
        ├── defaults
        │   └── main.yml
        ├── files           --> any files which we   need to copy to remote sever we place here
        ├── handlers        --> handelers will righte here
        │   └── main.yml
        ├── meta            --> config values
        │   └── main.yml
        ├── tasks           
        │   └── main.yml
        ├── templates
        ├── tests
        │   ├── inventory
        │   └── test.yml
        └── vars
            └── main.yml


difference between roles and playbook
-------------------------------------
A playbook is a YAML file that defines tasks and execution flow, whereas a role is a structured way of organizing those tasks into reusable components. Roles improve maintainability and scalability, especially in large projects.